    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the FEA model ensemble demonstrates High assurance for the intended COU. All 13 V&V 40 factors were assessed; twelve of thirteen factors met or exceeded their required gradation levels. The team judged that the overall body of evidence, including multi-laboratory experimental validation (N=11), rigorous mesh convergence, and E/uval values well below threshold for all QoIs, supports a High assurance level declaration. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved Gradation 1 versus required Gradation 3) was noted but considered acceptable by the team given the strong performance of all other factors.",
